The paper deals with the problem of windrose-planar drawings of planar graphs, which involves both combinatorial and geometric aspects. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents a characterization of plane triangulations admitting a windrose-planar drawing, which involves graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, windrose-planar drawings allow for the visualization of partial orders defined by the edges of the graph, which relates to information science (cs.SI).
